.TH "snd_ctl_replace" 9 "snd_ctl_replace" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ctl_replace \- replace the control instance of the card
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ctl_replace
.BI "(struct snd_card *card "  ","
.BI "struct snd_kcontrol *kcontrol "  ","
.BI "bool add_on_replace "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "card" 12
the card instance
.IP "kcontrol" 12
the control instance to replace
.IP "add_on_replace" 12
add the control if not already added
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Replaces the given control.  If the given control does not exist
and the add_on_replace flag is set, the control is added.  If the
control exists, it is destroyed first.

It frees automatically the control which cannot be added or replaced.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
